<p>Ready for some extra help factoring algebraic expressions? We're trying =
something new here. FreeMathHelp.com is adding our first AI-powered solver =
tool to assist with learning. We know AI offers some compelling advantages =
with math tutoring in particular - and that doesn't mean just getting answe=
rs blindly. Working through a step-by-step tutoring engine is a great way t=
o practice and solve a tricky problem.</p>

<p>Don't rely on any one tool to do all the work for you, and <strong>alway=
s check your work</strong> for correctness!</p>

<p><strong>Step 1: </strong>Enter your equation in the box below.</p>
<p><strong>Step 2: </strong>Click "Solve!"</p>

<div class=3D"input-group">
    <label for=3D"question">Enter your equation (must have one variable):</=
label><br>
    <textarea id=3D"question" rows=3D"3" placeholder=3D"E.g., 2x + 5 =3D 13=
 or 3t - 7 =3D 20"></textarea>
</div>

<button id=3D"calculateBtn">Solve!</button>

<div id=3D"resultContainer" class=3D"result-container">
    <div id=3D"stepsContainer"></div>
    <div id=3D"progressIndicator" class=3D"progress-indicator"></div>
</div>

<h3>How does it work?</h3>
<p>Enter your equation in the box above and click the button to submit your=
 question. Your input should be limited only to equations with one variable=
 (see examples below). Please be patient while our AI engine processes your=
 request. If you're not sure what to enter, look over the sample problems b=
elow to see the types of equations this tool can solve. The solver has been=
 tweaked specifically to provide step-by-step instruction, not just an answ=
er. Remember the idea is to *learn* -- not to copy solutions blindly. As th=
e solver matures, this will become more clear as the ability to generate la=
rge numbers of final answers will be restricted, and users will have to par=
ticipate in the solving process.</p>

<p>This is a brand new feature to FreeMathHelp.com -- give it a whirl and s=
ee what you think!</p>

<div class=3D"examples">
    <h3>Try solving:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>2x + 5 =3D 13</li>
        <li>3y - 7 =3D 20</li>
        <li>t/4 + 3 =3D 7</li>
        <li>5(n - 2) =3D 15</li>
        <li>z^2 - 4 =3D 0</li>
    </ul>
</div>

